name: Hearty Fish Chowder from Reynolds Wrap®
author: Reynolds Kitchens(R)
summary: This creamy, hearty chowder is a hassle-free meal for a busy day ahead.
ingredients: 1 (10.75 ounce) can  condensed cream of celery soup
1 (10 ounce) package frozen whole kernel corn
1 (10 ounce) package frozen baby lima beans
⅓ cup dry white wine or chicken broth
1 pound fresh or frozen cod or other whitefish fillets
⅓ cup nonfat dry milk powder
directions: Line a 5- to 6-quart slow cooker with a Reynolds® Slow Cooker Liner
Open slow cooker liner and place it inside a slow cooker bowl
Fit liner snugly against the bottom and sides of bowl; pull top of liner over rim of bowl
Combine potatoes, onion, garlic, cream of celery soup, corn, lima beans, broth, white wine and lemon-pepper seasoning
Cover and cook on low-heat setting for 6 to 7 hours or on high-heat setting for 3 to 3 1/2 hours
Rinse fish; pat dry with paper towels
Place fish on the mixture in the cooker
If using low-heat setting, turn to high-heat setting
Cover and cook for 1 hour more
Add undrained tomatoes and nonfat dry milk powder to cooker, stirring gently to break up the fish
Carefully remove lid to allow steam to escape
Serve directly from slow cooker liner using a wooden or plastic utensil
Do not lift or transport liner with food inside
Cool slow cooker completely; remove liner and toss
